{"meta":{"category_id":"head_of_ai_eea","category_name":"Head of AI — EEA","macro_family":"ai_leadership","priority":"primary_target","confidence":"high","total_jobs":38,"deep_analysis_count":21,"low_sample_mode":false,"noisy_title_mode":true,"uncertainty_note":"Category label is materially noisier than the underlying market evidence. Titles skew senior IC, architect, and player-coach rather than formal AI executive leadership, so this blueprint privileges role scope, architecture, delivery, and management evidence over literal title strings."},"category_signature":{"one_sentence_summary":"Despite the category label, this market behaves like an architecture-heavy, production-focused AI platform role: senior IC or player-coach scope dominates, platform design is near-universal, and wins come from delivery, reliability, evaluation, and stakeholder translation rather than formal org leadership.","distinctive_signals":["Role scope is not executive-heavy: senior IC 33/38 (86.8%), IC 22/38 (57.9%), player-coach 12/38 (31.6%), manager 2/38 (5.3%), director 2/38 (5.3%).","Architecture proof is the clearest anchor: platform design appears in 36/38 roles (94.7%), and architecture is a valued evidence type in 21/21 deep analyses (100.0%).","Production AI quality matters more than research framing: delivery 20/21 (95.2%), reliability 17/21 (81.0%), evaluation 11/21 (52.4%), governance 10/21 (47.6%), while research-heavy roles are only 4/38 (10.5%) and PhD requirement is 0/38 (0.0%)."],"citations":["Role scope distribution: senior_ic 33/38 (86.8%), IC 22/38 (57.9%), player_coach 12/38 (31.6%), manager 2/38 (5.3%), director 2/38 (5.3%).","Architecture and platform design: 36/38 (94.7%); valued evidence type architecture: 21/21 (100.0%).","Deep analysis valued evidence: delivery 20/21 (95.2%), reliability 17/21 (81.0%), evaluation 11/21 (52.4%), governance 10/21 (47.6%); research_heavy 4/38 (10.5%), requires_phd 0/38 (0.0%)."]},"headline_pattern":{"recommended_structure":"<Architect / Lead / Principal-level title if true> | Production AI Platform Architecture | Delivery, Reliability, Evaluation & Governance","safe_title_families":["AI Architect / Enterprise Architect","Staff / Principal / Lead Engineer, AI Platform","Technical Lead / Player-Coach, AI Systems","Engineering Manager only when direct people management is explicitly evidenced"],"safe_title_variants":["AI Architect","Enterprise Architect","Lead AI Engineer","Principal Engineer, AI Platform","Technical Lead, AI Systems"],"avoid_title_variants":["Head of AI","VP of AI","Chief AI Officer","Director of AI Research","Applied ML Scientist"],"evidence_first_rules":["Lead with architecture-forward scope because platform design appears in 36/38 roles (94.7%) while hiring is 2/38 (5.3%), org-building is 4/38 (10.5%), and budget/P&L is 0/38 (0.0%).","Do not force a literal executive title into the headline unless it was the real title; noisy_title_mode is true and senior IC scope is 33/38 (86.8%).","Name production AI proof, not generic AI ambition: emphasize delivery 20/21 (95.2%), reliability 17/21 (81.0%), evaluation 11/21 (52.4%), and governance 10/21 (47.6%).","Do not overfit the headline around one hard skill because no technical keyword is universal; the strongest language signal is Python at 14/38 (36.8%), with AWS and Kubernetes each 9/38 (23.7%).","ATS repetition strategy: strongest 4-6 keywords = 2-3 mentions across headline/profile/experience/skills if true; secondary 4-6 keywords = 1-2 mentions if true; niche keywords = once only and only if true."],"citations":["Title families are noisy: senior_engineer 18/38 (47.4%), ai_architect 4/38 (10.5%), engineering_manager 4/38 (10.5%), solutions_architect 4/38 (10.5%); noisy_title_mode=true.","Management evidence is weak: hiring 2/38 (5.3%), performance management 3/38 (7.9%), org_building 4/38 (10.5%), budget_pnl 0/38 (0.0%).","Hard-skill distribution is fragmented: Python 14/38 (36.8%), AWS 9/38 (23.7%), Kubernetes 9/38 (23.7%)."]},"tagline_profile_angle":{"positioning_angle":["Position as the person who turns AI concepts into production architecture, integration patterns, and reliable delivery: platform design 36/38 (94.7%), delivery 20/21 (95.2%), reliability 17/21 (81.0%).","Position as a hands-on architect or player-coach who can mentor and translate across teams without overstating org ownership: mentoring 18/38 (47.4%), collaboration 31/38 (81.6%), communication 26/38 (68.4%), hiring 2/38 (5.3%)."],"foreground":["Architecture blueprints and system design for production AI platforms.","Delivery outcomes: shipped systems, scaled services, improved quality, shortened cycle times.","Reliability, observability, evaluation, and guardrails in production settings.","Cross-functional translation across engineering, product, and enterprise stakeholders."],"avoid":["Executive-org language that implies headcount, budget, or formal business ownership.","Research-centered framing, publication emphasis, or model-scientist positioning.","Claims of owning end-to-end MLOps, vector database architecture, or custom LLM training unless explicitly evidenced.","Region-specific compliance or domain authority claims unless repeated and provable."],"safe_positioning":["Production AI architect with delivery and reliability evidence.","Hands-on technical lead for AI integrations, orchestration, and governance.","Player-coach mentor who improves system quality and team execution without inflating people-management scope."],"unsafe_positioning":["AI executive / business owner with budget or P&L accountability.","Research-led ML scientist or custom-model lead.","Formal people manager with a sizeable reporting line.","Regulated-industry AI governance lead without explicit compliance ownership."],"citations":["Soft skills: collaboration 31/38 (81.6%), communication 26/38 (68.4%), mentoring 18/38 (47.4%).","Management evidence remains limited: hiring 2/38 (5.3%), performance management 3/38 (7.9%), org_building 4/38 (10.5%), budget_pnl 0/38 (0.0%).","Unsafe claims in deep analysis include budget/P&L, custom LLM training, mechanistic interpretability, patents/publications, full MLOps ownership, vector database architecture, and formal people management; each appears only 1-2 times across 21 deep analyses."]},"core_competency_themes":[{"section_name":"Architecture Proof","themes":[{"theme":"Platform architecture and system design","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"Show concrete architecture ownership because platform design appears in 36/38 roles (94.7%) and architecture is the top valued evidence type in 21/21 deep analyses (100.0%).","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: \"platform architecture\", \"system design\", \"enterprise architecture\", \"scalability\", \"microservices\". Use 2-3 mentions across headline/profile/experience/skills.","citation":"Platform design 36/38 (94.7%); architecture as valued evidence 21/21 (100.0%); microservices 8/38 (21.1%)."},{"theme":"Greenfield plus optimization delivery","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Show both new-build and improvement work because roles often expect more than pure greenfield; greenfield+optimization appears in 20/38 roles (52.6%), versus greenfield-only 2/38 (5.3%) and optimization-only 4/38 (10.5%).","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: \"greenfield\", \"modernization\", \"performance tuning\", \"re-architecture\". Use 1-2 mentions in experience bullets.","citation":"Greenfield split: both 20/38 (52.6%), greenfield 2/38 (5.3%), optimization 4/38 (10.5%)."},{"theme":"Cloud-native implementation depth","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"Cloud and container signals are useful proof of execution, but no single stack dominates enough to define the category alone.","ats_guidance":"Use only true stack terms. Strongest stack keywords can appear 2-3 times if central; otherwise keep AWS, Kubernetes, Docker, Terraform, Azure, or GCP to 1-2 mentions.","citation":"AWS 9/38 (23.7%), Kubernetes 9/38 (23.7%), Docker 8/38 (21.1%), Terraform 5/38 (13.2%), Azure 4/38 (10.5%), multi-cloud preference 9/38 (23.7%)."}]},{"section_name":"Production AI Quality","themes":[{"theme":"Evaluation and quality controls","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Evaluation is a recurring differentiator in production AI roles, especially where trustworthy outputs and production readiness matter.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: \"evaluation\", \"quality framework\", \"acceptance criteria\", \"offline/online testing\". Use 2-3 mentions across profile and achievement bullets.","citation":"Evaluation-quality signal 8/38 (21.1%), evaluation frameworks 4/38 (10.5%), evaluation as valued evidence 11/21 (52.4%)."},{"theme":"Reliability and observability","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"Production roles value systems that stay healthy and debuggable; reliability is cited in 17/21 deep analyses (81.0%), ahead of most named AI methods.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: \"reliability\", \"observability\", \"SLOs\", \"incident reduction\", \"Datadog\". Use 1-2 mentions unless a major achievement depends on it.","citation":"Reliability as valued evidence 17/21 (81.0%); observability 6/38 (15.8%); Datadog 3/38 (7.9%)."},{"theme":"Guardrails, governance, and responsible rollout","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Governance appears more often as delivery control than as formal compliance leadership; show practical guardrails and approval logic, not inflated policy ownership.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: \"guardrails\", \"governance\", \"policy controls\", \"auditability\". Use 1-2 mentions; niche compliance terms once only and only if true.","citation":"Guardrails/governance 5/38 (13.2%); governance as valued evidence 10/21 (47.6%); GDPR 2/38 (5.3%), data privacy 2/38 (5.3%)."}]},{"section_name":"Delivery And Influence","themes":[{"theme":"Cross-functional collaboration and communication","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This category repeatedly asks for stakeholder translation and multi-team execution, with collaboration and communication leading all soft-skill signals.","ats_guidance":"Strongest soft-skill keywords if true: \"collaboration\", \"communication\", \"stakeholder alignment\", \"cross-functional\". Use 2-3 mentions across summary and experience.","citation":"Collaboration 31/38 (81.6%), communication 26/38 (68.4%), stakeholder management 7/38 (18.4%), cross-functional collaboration 4/38 (10.5%)."},{"theme":"Mentoring without overstating people management","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Mentoring strengthens player-coach credibility, but formal people management is rare. Show technical guidance, design review, and coaching rather than claiming org leadership.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: \"mentoring\", \"technical leadership\", \"design reviews\", \"coaching\". Use 1-2 mentions in work history.","citation":"Mentoring 18/38 (47.4%), technical leadership 5/38 (13.2%); hiring 2/38 (5.3%), performance management 3/38 (7.9%), org_building 4/38 (10.5%)."},{"theme":"Execution speed and process improvement","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Deep analyses reward delivery proof, and pain points include backlog growth, long cycle times, weak review quality, and remote-team friction.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: \"delivery\", \"cycle time\", \"process optimization\", \"automation\", \"developer productivity\". Use 1-2 mentions tied to measurable outcomes.","citation":"Delivery as valued evidence 20/21 (95.2%); pain points include increase productivity (1 mention), backlogs expand (1), cycle times stretch (1), code review quality degrades (1), remote-team obstacle removal (1)."}]},{"section_name":"Applied AI Integration","themes":[{"theme":"RAG and agent workflow integration","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Applied AI signals exist, but mostly as integration and orchestration work rather than frontier-model ownership. Use them when they were production responsibilities.","ats_guidance":"Strongest AI-method keywords if true: \"RAG\", \"workflow orchestration\", \"agents\", \"retrieval\", \"LangGraph\". Use 2-3 mentions if central; niche frameworks once only.","citation":"RAG 5/38 (13.2%), agents_orchestration 5/38 (13.2%), LangChain 2/38 (5.3%), LangGraph 2/38 (5.3%)."},{"theme":"Hands-on engineering depth without overfitting one language","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"Show that you still build and debug systems. There is no single universal technical keyword in this category, so emphasize credible engineering depth instead of forcing one stack.","ats_guidance":"Strongest 4-6 true keywords can appear 2-3 times. For languages, repeat your real primary language 2-3 times and keep secondary languages to 1-2 mentions.","citation":"Python 14/38 (36.8%), Java 8/38 (21.1%), PHP 4/38 (10.5%), TypeScript 3/38 (7.9%), Go 2/38 (5.3%); no hard skill reaches 60.0%."},{"theme":"Enterprise integration and stakeholder translation","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"A meaningful slice of the market is consultancy or enterprise SaaS, and explicit pain points include integrating partner APIs and delivering value in global environments.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: \"API integration\", \"enterprise systems\", \"partner platforms\", \"stakeholder translation\". Use 1-2 mentions in relevant roles.","citation":"Pain point: integrate with global partner APIs (2 mentions); consulting 5/38 (13.2%), enterprise SaaS 4/38 (10.5%), remote_first 19/38 (50.0%)."}]}],"key_achievement_archetypes":[{"rank":1,"archetype":"Architecture blueprint turned into production AI platform","what_it_proves":"Proves category fit on the strongest market signal: architecture ownership tied to real delivery, scalability, and production adoption.","pain_points_addressed":["deliver value quickly in a high-growth global environment","improve performance, quality, and communication across departments"],"metrics_to_include":["systems or services launched","adoption or tenant count","latency / throughput / uptime","deployment frequency","time-to-production"],"story_format_guidance":"Start with the platform constraint, name the architecture decision, then quantify delivery and scale outcomes. End with how the design improved production readiness or cross-team execution.","citation":"Platform design 36/38 (94.7%); architecture evidence 21/21 (100.0%); delivery evidence 20/21 (95.2%); scale evidence 16/21 (76.2%)."},{"rank":2,"archetype":"Reliability and observability uplift for AI or integration workflows","what_it_proves":"Proves the candidate can productionize AI systems beyond demos by improving resilience, traceability, and operational confidence.","pain_points_addressed":["eliminate obstacles for a remote engineering team","code review devolves into perfunctory approval"],"metrics_to_include":["incident rate","MTTR","SLO attainment","error budget burn","alert volume","debug time"],"story_format_guidance":"Use an ARIS structure: baseline instability, intervention in observability or reliability design, measurable service improvement, then resulting team efficiency. Keep it operational and quantified.","citation":"Reliability evidence 17/21 (81.0%); observability 6/38 (15.8%); Datadog 3/38 (7.9%)."},{"rank":3,"archetype":"Evaluation and guardrails implementation for trustworthy outputs","what_it_proves":"Proves applied AI maturity by showing the candidate can raise quality, reduce risk, and make outputs more dependable in production environments.","pain_points_addressed":["transparent and trustworthy recommendations for security professionals","production-ready genai solutions"],"metrics_to_include":["quality score improvement","hallucination or error reduction","acceptance rate","manual review reduction","policy violation rate"],"story_format_guidance":"Frame the problem as output quality or trust risk, specify the evaluation or guardrail mechanism, then quantify the gain in acceptance, quality, or safety. Avoid policy-leadership claims unless they were formal responsibilities.","citation":"Evaluation evidence 11/21 (52.4%); evaluation-quality 8/38 (21.1%); guardrails/governance 5/38 (13.2%); governance evidence 10/21 (47.6%)."},{"rank":4,"archetype":"Partner or enterprise integration architecture across distributed systems","what_it_proves":"Proves the candidate can connect AI or platform capabilities into real business environments, especially across partner APIs, enterprise constraints, and cross-team dependencies.","pain_points_addressed":["integrate with global partner apis","deliver value quickly in a high-growth global environment"],"metrics_to_include":["integration count","partner onboarding time","failure rate reduction","throughput","customer or internal-user adoption"],"story_format_guidance":"Describe the enterprise integration challenge, the routing or orchestration design, and the measured effect on delivery speed, reliability, or usability. Keep the emphasis on system integration, not speculative AI novelty.","citation":"Pain point: integrate with global partner APIs (2 mentions); consulting 5/38 (13.2%), enterprise SaaS 4/38 (10.5%), cybersecurity 3/38 (7.9%), fintech 3/38 (7.9%)."},{"rank":5,"archetype":"Delivery acceleration through process, automation, and mentoring","what_it_proves":"Proves player-coach value: the candidate improves team output and engineering quality without needing inflated org-builder claims.","pain_points_addressed":["increase team productivity through process optimization, automation, and efficiency improvements","backlogs expand","cycle times stretch across weeks"],"metrics_to_include":["cycle time","lead time","PR turnaround","defect escape rate","team throughput","automation coverage"],"story_format_guidance":"Show the execution bottleneck, the process or automation change, and the quantified throughput or quality gain. Add mentoring or design-review influence only if it directly contributed to the result.","citation":"Delivery evidence 20/21 (95.2%); mentoring 18/38 (47.4%); pain points on productivity, backlog growth, and cycle time each appear in deep analysis."}],"role_weighting_guidance":{"highest_weight_roles":["AI / Platform Architect","Principal or Staff Engineer with AI platform ownership","Technical Lead / Player-Coach for AI systems and integrations"],"expand_in_work_history":["Roles where you owned architecture decisions, platform design, or enterprise integration patterns.","Roles where AI-related systems reached production and you can quantify delivery, reliability, evaluation, or governance outcomes.","Roles where you mentored engineers, led design reviews, or translated across engineering, product, and stakeholder groups.","Remote or distributed delivery roles when you improved execution or communication in those environments."],"compress_in_work_history":["Pure people-management roles with limited technical ownership.","Research-only work, publication-style framing, or model-science claims that did not drive shipped systems.","Older roles that do not support distributed systems, integration, cloud, or architecture credibility.","Domain claims that are weakly evidenced, such as formal regulated-environment governance leadership."],"how_to_frame_non_ai_experience":["Translate distributed systems, microservices, cloud, API integration, and observability work into the foundations of AI productionization.","Map quality, testing, governance, or reliability work from non-AI systems into production AI readiness rather than pretending the work was AI-native.","Use AI-specific terminology only where the work truly involved AI features, AI platforms, RAG, orchestration, evaluation, or guardrails."],"citations":["Role scope: IC 22/38 (57.9%), player_coach 12/38 (31.6%), manager 2/38 (5.3%), director 2/38 (5.3%).","Architecture/delivery/reliability dominate deep analysis: 21/21 (100.0%), 20/21 (95.2%), 17/21 (81.0%).","Management evidence is weak: hiring 2/38 (5.3%), org_building 4/38 (10.5%), budget_pnl 0/38 (0.0%)."]},"language_and_tone":{"recommended_tone":"architect","formality":"high","preferred_vocabulary":["platform architecture","production AI","system design","delivery ownership","reliability","observability","evaluation","guardrails","governance","integration","scalability","mentoring"],"avoid_vocabulary":["P&L ownership","AI visionary","thought leader","research lead","built custom LLMs from scratch","formal org builder","Chief AI Officer"],"citations":["Architecture and production evidence dominate: platform design 36/38 (94.7%), delivery 20/21 (95.2%), reliability 17/21 (81.0%), evaluation 11/21 (52.4%).","Soft-skill framing should stay collaborative and technical: collaboration 31/38 (81.6%), communication 26/38 (68.4%), mentoring 18/38 (47.4%).","Executive/business ownership language is weakly supported: hiring 2/38 (5.3%), org_building 4/38 (10.5%), budget_pnl 0/38 (0.0%)."]},"unsafe_or_weak_framing":{"avoid_claims":["Budget, P&L, or business-unit ownership unless explicitly evidenced.","Designed and trained custom LLMs from scratch as the primary model scientist.","Implemented mechanistic interpretability, patents, or publication-driven AI research as a core duty.","Owned the full MLOps stack for multiple programs as a dedicated ML platform architect.","Implemented vector database and embedding architecture beyond what the actual role required.","Led a formal team of integration engineers with direct people-management authority unless reporting lines are explicit."],"buzzword_patterns":["\"AI transformation leader\" without architecture or delivery proof.","\"Agentic AI expert\" without shipped orchestration, evaluation, or governance evidence.","\"GenAI strategist\" when the record is mainly engineering execution.","\"End-to-end AI owner\" when responsibilities were scoped to integration, platform, or reliability.","\"Enterprise AI governance leader\" without formal compliance or policy ownership."],"title_inflation_risks":["Using \"Head of AI\" when the evidence is senior IC or player-coach: senior_ic 33/38 (86.8%), manager 2/38 (5.3%), director 2/38 (5.3%).","Using \"Engineering Manager\" when the record shows mentoring but not hiring or performance management: mentoring 18/38 (47.4%), hiring 2/38 (5.3%), performance management 3/38 (7.9%).","Using research titles in a delivery category: research_heavy 4/38 (10.5%), requires_phd 0/38 (0.0%).","Using domain-executive titles tied to governance or regulation when GDPR and data privacy appear only 2/38 times each (5.3%)."],"research_framing_risks":["Do not foreground publications, patents, or research programs; positive evidence is delivery-oriented and research-heavy roles are only 4/38 (10.5%).","Do not imply PhD-level scientific requirements; PhD requirement is 0/38 (0.0%).","Do not present the profile as pure applied ML science when the market favors architecture, delivery, reliability, and integration.","Keep AI-method references applied and production-bound rather than experimental."],"domain_or_region_risks":["Do not imply formal GDPR, PCI, or regulated-industry authority unless the CV shows direct ownership; GDPR 2/38 (5.3%), PCI 2/38 (5.3%), data privacy 2/38 (5.3%).","Do not claim native-language or country-specific requirements; native_language_requirements are absent in deep analysis.","Do not overstate healthcare, fintech, or cybersecurity specialization unless repeated in the candidate record; category spread is consulting 5/38 (13.2%), enterprise SaaS 4/38 (10.5%), cybersecurity 3/38 (7.9%), fintech 3/38 (7.9%), healthcare 2/38 (5.3%).","Do not imply broad EEA compliance leadership solely from the region label; the evidence supports remote/distributed delivery more strongly than regional policy depth."],"citations":["Deep-analysis unsafe claims are mostly singletons or low-frequency outliers across 21 analyses, not category norms.","Research-heavy signal is 4/38 (10.5%) and requires_phd is 0/38 (0.0%).","Governance/compliance terms are sparse: GDPR 2/38 (5.3%), data privacy 2/38 (5.3%), PCI 2/38 (5.3%)."]},"evidence_ledger":[{"recommendation":"Frame this category as architect or player-coach, not executive leader.","support":["Senior_ic 33/38 (86.8%), IC 22/38 (57.9%), player_coach 12/38 (31.6%).","Manager 2/38 (5.3%), director 2/38 (5.3%), hiring 2/38 (5.3%), budget_pnl 0/38 (0.0%)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Lead the CV with architecture proof tied to shipped production outcomes.","support":["Platform design 36/38 (94.7%).","Architecture 21/21 (100.0%) and delivery 20/21 (95.2%) are the strongest valued evidence types."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Show reliability, evaluation, and governance as production controls, not abstract quality language.","support":["Reliability 17/21 (81.0%), evaluation 11/21 (52.4%), governance 10/21 (47.6%).","Evaluation-quality 8/38 (21.1%), guardrails/governance 5/38 (13.2%), observability 6/38 (15.8%)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Keep AI-method language applied and integration-oriented.","support":["RAG 5/38 (13.2%) and agents_orchestration 5/38 (13.2%) appear, but model serving/routing is 0/38 (0.0%) and fine_tuning is 1/38 (2.6%).","Research-heavy roles are only 4/38 (10.5%)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Do not overfit the CV to one programming language or framework.","support":["No hard skill reaches 60.0%.","Python is the strongest language at 14/38 (36.8%); Java is 8/38 (21.1%); LangChain and LangGraph are each 2/38 (5.3%)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Use mentoring and cross-functional influence as leadership proof, but stop short of org-builder claims unless explicit.","support":["Collaboration 31/38 (81.6%), communication 26/38 (68.4%), mentoring 18/38 (47.4%).","Hiring 2/38 (5.3%), performance management 3/38 (7.9%), org_building 4/38 (10.5%)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Translate non-AI distributed-systems work into AI production readiness when direct AI tenure is limited.","support":["Microservices 8/38 (21.1%), AWS 9/38 (23.7%), Kubernetes 9/38 (23.7%), Docker 8/38 (21.1%).","Deep-analysis candidate mappings repeatedly connect orchestration, routing, integration, and reliability work to category fit."],"confidence":"medium"},{"recommendation":"Only claim compliance, regional governance, or regulated-domain depth when directly evidenced on the CV.","support":["GDPR 2/38 (5.3%), data privacy 2/38 (5.3%), PCI 2/38 (5.3%).","Native language requirements are absent; research/publication and formal governance claims appear mostly as unsafe outliers in deep analysis."],"confidence":"high"} 	
